  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd1 \u0db6\u0dad\u0dad\u0dca \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dc3\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "At night, rice is prepared in the presidential palace",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Photographs are being shared on the Internet showing that the fighters who took over Fort President House are preparing to cook rice at night after playing water sports in the swimming pool of the President House.",
        "The activists who entered the presidential palace were also seen walking in the rooms and sitting in comfortable seats making tea and drinking.",
        "Some people climbed onto the roof of the President's House and waved national flags and cheered.",
        "The security guards guarding the Presidential Palace were also seen leaving the buses this afternoon. Later, the activists also held a press conference at the President's House. They asked the people not to damage any public property."
      ],
